        "subject": "LU-925 agl: process CLO_REENQUEUED for lov lock enqueue",
        "message": "LU-925 agl: process CLO_REENQUEUED for lov lock enqueue\n\nThe osc_lock_wait() will re-trigger lock enqueue for non-granted\nAGL lock and return 'CLO_REENQUEUED' to the caller. Original lov\nlock enqueue logic ignored such case for lov_lock_enqueue_one(),\nso caused unexpected LASSERT when checking the result.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <yong.fan@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I499122bb696e0526771c9b543df98c2fd9cdb2c4\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
